isIsolated

boolean isIsolated()
Checks whether this multiple update transaction runs in isolated mode, i.e. each underlying record will be committed in an independent transaction, or not.

Returns:
true isolated mode is enabled, otherwise false

getCompletionError

java.lang.Exception getCompletionError(IDataRecord record)
                                       throws java.lang.IllegalStateException
Checks whether for the given record a transaction completion error has occurred. This might happen due to various reasons, e.g. required fields missing, constraint violations, application specific business exceptions, etc. Nevertheless only user exceptions will be handled. All other exceptions will cause IDataTransaction.commit() to fail.

Parameters:
record - the record to check for a completion error
Returns:
the completion error or null
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalStateException - if transaction has not been committed or closed
See Also:
IDataMultiUpdateTableRecord.getAssociatedTransaction(), UserException, UserRuntimeException

getCompletionErrorCount

int getCompletionErrorCount()
                            throws java.lang.IllegalStateException
Returns the complete error count for this transaction.
Useful for status message and user notification.

Returns:
the count of non committed/canceled records.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalStateException - if transaction has not been committed or closed
